/-------------\
| Description |

PCSpk is a set of command-line applications-clients for playing simple sounds,
mellodies using pc-speaker by any user with netcat server based on great
Johnathan Nightingale's beep (http://www.johnath.com/beep/).

/----------------\
| Implementation |

Dirty, awful, insecure, etc. but it works.
Using Johnathan Nightingale's beep, based on netcat and small C progs.

/---------------\
| Documentation |

beep - go to http://www.johnath.com/beep/
freq2beep & note2beep - reads from stdin

- freq2beep
space seperated values f[:l], where:
f is integer - frequency (in Hz)
l is integer - length (in ms), default: 100

- note2beep
first 3-digit number is integer - tempo (bpm)
next are space seperated values TOL, where:
T is letter - tone: C,d(des),D,e(es),E,F,g(ges),G,a(as),A,B,H,P(pause)
O is digit - octave: 0-9
L is digit/letter - length: L=0-9,A-Z <=> 1/(L+1)

/--------------\
| Requirements |

Great Johnathan Nightingale's beep, that beeps the PC speaker with control of
frequency, duration, repetitions, etc. (http://www.johnath.com/beep/)

/-------------------\
| Examples of usage |

fuga - J.S.Bach fugue in D minor (fragment)
fuga2 - J.S.Bach fugue in D minor (longer fragment)
cosmic - wtf? ;-)

